<title>HONG KONG: Kelon proposes expanding share capital.</title>
<headline>Kelon proposes expanding share capital.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-03-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>Guangdong Kelon Electrical Holdings Co Ltd said on Thursday it would seek shareholder approval at an annual general meeting on April 28 to issue up to 76.6 million new H shares.</p>
<p>The Chinese refrigerator maker said it would authorise company directors to issue new shares not exceeding 20 percent of the amount of existing shares in the 12-month period after Chinese authorities grant approval.</p>
<p>Last month, Guangdong Kelon said it was considering expanding share capital as one way of raising money to fund its production expansion plan.</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2843 6370</p>
